{
  "texts": [
    "In contrast, vipr achieves excellent agreement with the ground truth, accurately reconstructing even irregular boundaries and detailed internal features.A more quantitative evaluation is provided in table 9, where we assess prediction accuracy at the level of individual objects.",
    "Specifically, we measure the fraction of the Lagrangian volume (within both the R Lag and R max) that is assigned to the true mass class by each model.",
    "Although this quantity does not correspond exactly to the halo mass, it serves as a practical proxy for object-level accuracy in the absence of a fragmentation step that would 6, but for the six representative halos described in Table 8.",
    "Each slice intersects the respective proto-halo patch along a plane containing the center of mass and oriented perpendicular to one of the Cartesian axes of the simulation box.",
    "In each panel, the inner circle denotes the Lagrangian radius corresponding to a spherical proto-halo of that mass, while the outer circle indicates the maximum proto-halo radius R max, defined as the farthest distance from the center of mass to any voxel in the ground truth mask."
  ]
}